Key Match Events: The Phillies scored a season-high 16 runs in their 16-2 rout of the Marlins
Zack Wheeler allowed one run in six innings, lowering his season ERA to 2.59
Pre-Game Insights: Edward Cabrera was scratched an hour before first pitch with migraine-like symptoms
Post-Match Reflections: Trea Turner commented on the adjustment of facing a different pitcher after Cabrera was scratched
Miscellaneous Highlights: J.T. Realmuto exited in the fourth with a left knee contusion
Others: Rob Thomson commented on Wheeler's performance and his potential Cy Young Award bid
The Phillies' offense racked up 22 hits, a season high, with all nine starters having at least one hit
